metadata.name: Syzers #187
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

¬∑¬∑¬∑¬∑ On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ¬∑¬∑¬∑¬∑

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template. 
"FXHASH PFP Token Generator" https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

for best resolution "open live" then use the "download image" button on the lower right corner ;)

metadata.name: hollow #16
metadata.description:
In 1993, Basque sculptor Eduardo Chillida proposed a project to create an immense void inside Tindaya, the Sacred Mountain of Fuerteventura's indigenous inhabitants. The hollow cube measuring approximately 45 x 50 x 65 meters was conceived as a space for "all the people" to "fully experience the tininess of humankind".

The idea of the project dates back to the 1980s, and it took the artist years of searching for the ideal mountain in different parts of the world. However, what was ideal for Chillida evoked a lot of controversy due to the environmental and social impact of the project. There was uncertainty about Tindaya's structural feasibility and the potential harm to the ancient petroglyphs engraved on its surface. What's more, the financial sustainability of the project's economic model would depend on hundreds of thousands of tourists visiting the site each year, converting a work of art into a holiday attraction.

Chillida called his project the Monument to Tolerance. Although it never came into existence, it has caused division and conflict since it was conceived.


"hollow" is an exploration of 256 voids in nonexistent natural monuments. Made of digital matter instead of stone and lacking cultural charge, its sole purpose is to contemplate the tininess of humankind.


-----

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the quality from preview to the resolution of a print of approximately 30cm in height. In live mode, click on PNG to save the rendered image.

Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes from a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones to render the image. 

Requirements: 1GB of RAM. The system needs up to 200 MB of free RAM for rendering square preview images and up to 400 MB of free RAM for rendering square images at the highest resolution. I tested on Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge / Windows, Mac OS, Android, and iPhone, but please make sure it works on your device before minting.

-----

Possible features:

color scheme: cairngorm, alborz, bardenas, atlas, bieszczady, watkins

proportions: square, wide, standard, narrow

frame: none, vignette, bright, dark, bright with vignette, dark with vignette

visitors: tourists, tourists and birds, solitary flock of birds, only light

metadata.name: Humanity #17
metadata.description:
In a modern society everyone tries to dictate his own rules of life, where is no place for emotions and sincere feelings. Those concrete jungles are more like giant anthills.
People are interchangeable gears in one big mechanism, today you are here and tomorrow.. who knows. Tomorrow you could be gone.

New element, same functionality, you won`t find something new. Humanity is on the right path to globalization and unification. We are entitled to agreed points.
You can`t be who you are. Sooner or later, you`re going to have to be an interchangeable element. 
The rules of this life have been written for you.

Polina Arz ¬©

A professional Fashion designer and fashion artist whose work reflects the spirit of modernity and the world around us in the language of current trends and contemporary art.

metadata.name: Totalistic Cellular Automata #326
metadata.description:
Totalistic Cellular Automata is a work celebrating my appreciation and love for 1D Cellular Automata. In this piece there are many different rules and rulesets which dictate how the cells will behave. Totalistic cellular automata is a type of cellular automata where the total or average values of cells in a neighborhood are what the rules depend on.

Clicking the image continues or pauses the generation.

There are 4 dimension sizes, 4 possible states, 52 possible rulesets, and 55 colorways. 

This generator was inspired by the works and discoveries of Stephen Wolfram and ‚ÄúRGB Elementary Cellular Automata‚Äù by Ciphrd which will always have a special place in my heart.

JohnWow(2022)

metadata.name: de|growth:generations #34
metadata.description:
Materials tend to take particular forms due to their physical properties, technological necessities or natural limitations. However, what rules should a simulated environment follow when no physical constraints are inherent to the digital environment?

This project continues the exploration of shaping digital matter that I began on hicetnunc in 2021. Each token creates an image of a unique sculpture generated with a custom growth/degrowth algorithm. The image is rendered with a tailored raytracing script.

---
Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones for the 800x800px image.

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the resolution from preview quality to a print of approx. 30x30cm. There may be minor differences in tone or contrast for different resolutions.

In live mode:
Click PNG to save the rendered image.
Click STL to download the digital model to view on your computer or 3d print at home [experimental]
